---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Why I'm Deepening My Java Skills in 2026"
  description="Why Java is my favorite language, what I plan to study deeply this year, and how I will stay consistent."
>
  <article class="pt-28 pb-16 max-w-3xl">
    <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm font-medium text-primary hover:underline">← Back to blog</a>

    <header class="mt-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-muted">March 7, 2026</p>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-foreground">Why I'm Deepening My Java Skills in 2026</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-muted leading-relaxed">
        In my current role, I work across different technologies. Outside work, Java is the language I want to master deeply.
        This year, I'm making that commitment explicit.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="mt-10 space-y-6 text-[1.05rem] leading-8 text-secondary-foreground">
      <p>
        I have used Java before, but I want a stronger foundation at the level that matters in production: runtime behavior,
        memory, concurrency, and performance. Not just syntax.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground pt-2">What "Deep" Means For Me</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Understand Java evolution from <strong>8 to 25</strong> with engineering impact, not only feature lists.</li>
        <li>Study JVM internals: class loading, JIT compilation flow, and garbage collection trade-offs.</li>
        <li>Practice concurrency with modern Java patterns, including virtual threads.</li>
        <li>Use profiling and benchmarking tools to validate performance assumptions.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground pt-2">Execution Plan</h2>
      <p>
        I am starting with <strong>1 hour per day</strong> and focusing on consistency:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Reading and notes</li>
        <li>Hands-on experiments</li>
        <li>Weekly summary of what worked and what did not</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-foreground pt-2">Public Commitment</h2>
      <p>
        I will use this blog to publish concise updates: lessons learned, experiments, and practical takeaways from each step.
        The goal is simple: measurable progress, week after week.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>
